Package monkey.ai.table

Class SearchResult<Action>

  • java.lang.Object
    • monkey.ai.table.SearchResult<Action>
  • Type Parameters:
    Action - The type of the moves of the game.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<SearchResult<Action>>
    public class SearchResult<Action>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<SearchResult<Action>>
    A SearchResult stores the aftermath of a brute-force search. That is, the best/refutation move, the computed score, its nature, the depth of the search and the number of nodes visited in the process. The last field is an addition to the data usually found "traditional" transposition tables. It is meant to support the TWOBIG1 replacement scheme. See D.M. Breuker, J.W.H.M. Uiterwijk, H.J. van den Herik, Information in Transposition Tables, in H.J. van den Herik, J.W.H.M. Uiterwijk (eds), Advances in Computer Chess 8, Computer Science Department, Universiteit Maastricht. 1997, pp. 2-3, 4.
    Since:
    1.0
